COPS in the USA have launched a manhunt for an unidentified gunman who shot five family members as they attended a funeral on Thursday, 2 June. According to Daily Mail, the mourners were bidding farewell to Da’Shontay L King (37), who was killed in March. During the funeral at Graceland Cemetery in Racine at around 2.30pm, an unnamed gunman opened fire. In a statement, Racine Police Department said the victims were reportedly being treated at Ascension All Saints Hospital. READ: Two women shot dead, man turns gun on himself! “There were multiple shots fired at Graceland. There are victims but unknown how many at this time. The scene is still active and being investigated,” the statement read. It was reported that the deceased was shot dead by cops who were doing a stop and search on a busy road as part of a firearms investigation. “King got out of his vehicle armed with a gun. A cop reportedly ordered him to stop and comply with commands, but police say he refused, and the cop fired. The incident was caught on body cameras,” the article read.